What is a virtual environment in Python?

# Answear 1:
A virtual environment is a tool that allows 
you to create an isolated environment for your
Python projects.
This is useful because it allows you to install
packages and dependencies for one project without 
affecting other projects on your system.


 # Answear 2:
A: A virtual environment is a way of creating an 
isolated Python environment that is separate from 
the global Python environment on your system.
This allows you to install and manage Python
packages without affecting other Python applications
on your system. Virtual environments are created
using the venv module that comes with Python, 
and they can be activated and deactivated using the 
activate script that is generated when the virtual 
environment is created. To install packages within
a virtual environment, you can use
